\mt2 The continued account by
\mt1 Luke
\mt2 commonly called
\mt1 Acts
\is1 Introduction
\is2 Author
\ip This account commonly known as \bk The acts of the missionaries of Yeshua the Messiah\bk*, is the continuation of \bk The Good Message according to Luke\bk*, and unlike most other Bibles, the \em Open English Translation\em* places these two accounts one after the other.
\is2 This account
\ip The main purpose of this account is to tell about the actions of the first followers of Yeshua (Jesus) the messiah. God's spirit helped them to proclaim good message about him вҖңin Yerushalem (Jerusalem) and all across \add the provinces of\add* Yudea (Judaea) and Shomron (Samaria), and all the way to the furthest parts of the planetвҖқ (1:8).
\ip This document has three divisions related to the expanding circles as the good message from Yeshua the messiah spread wider and wider: (1) In \bd Yerushalem\bd* where the believers start to get organised after Yeshua ascended up into the clouds; (2) the work and the message spreads wider out to all of the district of \bd Yudea\bd*; and (3) spreading more widely again around the Mediterranean Ocean and all the way to \bd Rome\bd*.
\ip It's also documented here about how God's spirit came to the believers as they were together in a room in Yerushalem at the Festival of Pentecost (fifty days after The Passover). The spirit helps and gives wisdom and strength to the believers and teachers of believers.
\iot Main components of Luke's second account
\io1 The believers start to get organised \ior 1:1-26\ior*
\io2 a. The final command of Yeshua and his promise \ior 1:1-14\ior*
\io2 b. The replacing of Yudas/Judas \ior 1:15-26\ior*
\io1 Witnessing in Yerushalem/Jerusalem \ior 2:1вҖ“8:3\ior*
\io1 Expanding out to Yudea/Judaea and Shomron/Samaria \ior 8:4вҖ“12:25\ior*
\io1 Paul's activities \ior 13:1вҖ“28:31\ior*
\io2 a. Paul's first missionary trip \ior 13:1вҖ“14:28\ior*
\io2 b. The conference in Yerushalem \ior 15:1-35\ior*
\io2 c. Paul's second missionary trip \ior 15:36вҖ“18:22\ior*
\io2 d. Paul's third missionary trip \ior 18:23вҖ“21:16\ior*
\io2 e. Paul is imprisoned in Yerushalem, taken to Caesarea, and from there to Rome \ior 21:17вҖ“28:31\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Introduction
\rem /s1 The Promise of the Holy Spirit; Jesus Taken Up Into Heaven
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 1:1: \xt Luk 1:1-4.\x*Dear TheofilusВҰ81661, I wrote my firstВҰ81655 accountВҰ81656 about all the things thatВҰ81662 \nd Yeshua\nd* beganВҰ81663 to do andВҰ81668 to teachВҰ81669
\v 2 untilВҰ81670 the dayВҰ81672 when he was takenВҰ81682 up\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Luk 24:51.\x* \add into the sky\add* after, with the help of the holy \nd spiritВҰ81678\nd*, havingВҰ81674 commandedВҰ81674 the missionaries that he had chosenВҰ81681.
\s1 Yeshua, alive, tells them to wait
\p
\v 3 After the timeВҰ81696 of his sufferingВҰ81697, Yeshua presentedВҰ81692 himselfВҰ81693 to them in ways that were infallible proofsВҰ81701 \add that he was alive again\add*вҖ”appearingВҰ81706 to them and telling them about God's kingdomВҰ81715.
\v 4 \x + \xo 1:4: \xt Luk 24:49.\x*Once when they were togetherВҰ81719, he told them, вҖң\wj Don't leave Yerushalem, butВҰ81718 wait there for what was promisedВҰ81733 by the fatherВҰ81735, as you all have \+add already\+add* heardВҰ81737 me say.\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 1:5: \xt Mat 3:11; Mrk 1:8; Luk 3:16; Yhn 1:33.\x*\wj YohanВҰ81745 immersed \+add people\+add* in waterВҰ81748, but you all will be immersed in the holy \+nd spiritВҰ81753\+nd* in just a few daysВҰ81765.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's ascension
\rem /s1 The Ascension of Jesus; Jesus Is Taken Up to Heaven
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ81771 when they were \add next\add* gathered togetherВҰ81773, they asked himВҰ81776, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ81778\nd*, is this now the time when you'll be restoringВҰ81784 the kingdomВҰ81787 to YisraelВҰ81790?вҖқ\f + \fr 1:6 \ft At the time of asking, Israelis were burdened under the rule and taxes of the Roman occupiers.\f*
\p
\v 7 ButВҰ81796 Yeshua respondedВҰ81795 to them, вҖң\wj You don'tВҰ81799 need to knowВҰ81802 the timesВҰ81803 or seasonsВҰ81805 \+add when future events will happen\+add*вҖ”it's the fatherВҰ81808 who decides all thatВҰ81806.\wj*
\v 8 \x + \xo 1:8: \xt Mat 28:19; Mrk 16:15; Luk 24:47-48.\x*\wj However, you all will be receivingВҰ81815 powerВҰ81816 when the holy \+nd spiritВҰ81820\+nd* lands on you. Then you'll tell \+add people\+add* about me in Yerushalem and all across \+add the provinces of\+add* YudeaВҰ81835 and ShomronВҰ81837 \add (SamariaВҰ81837)\add*, and all the way to the furthest parts of the planet.\wj*вҖқ
\v 9 \x + \xo 1:9: \xt Mrk 16:19; Luk 24:50-51.\x*After he'd saidВҰ81846 that andВҰ81844 while they were still looking at him, he was liftedВҰ81853 up \add into the sky\add* until they could no longer see him because of the \add #clouds\add*.
\p
\v 10 As theyВҰ81868 stoodВҰ81878 there staring into the skyВҰ81871 after he'd gone, suddenly twoВҰ81877 menВҰ81876 in whiteВҰ81885 clothesВҰ81882 were standing beside them
\v 11 and said, вҖңYou men from GalileeВҰ81890! Why are you still standing there lookingВҰ81893 up at the sky? This \nd Yeshua\nd* who's been takenВҰ81902 up away from you into heaven will come back in the same way thatВҰ81901 you saw him go up into heaven.вҖқ
\s1 Matthias replaces Yudas Iscariot
\rem /s1 The church in Jerusalem; Matthias Chosen to Replace Judas; Matthias Replaces Judas; Judas' Successor
\p
\v 12 Then theyВҰ81919 walked down the MtВҰ81923. of OlivesВҰ81926 and returnedВҰ81919 to Yerushalem which was less than a kilometre away.
\v 13 \x + \xo 1:13: \xt Mat 10:2-4; Mrk 3:16-19; Luk 6:14-16.\x*They wentВҰ81944 into the upstairsВҰ81943 roomВҰ81943 whereВҰ81945 they were stayingВҰ81947вҖ”PeterВҰ81950 and Yohan, Yacob and AndrewВҰ81958, PhilipВҰ81959 and ThomasВҰ81961, BartholomewВҰ81962 and MatthewВҰ81964, Yacob (son of Alfeus), SimonВҰ81970 (the Zealot memberВҰ81972), and YudasВҰ81974 (son of Yacob).
\v 14 They were united in their ongoing prayersВҰ81983, along with MariaВҰ81993 the motherВҰ81995 of \nd Yeshua\nd*, and hisВҰ82002 brothersВҰ82001.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ82003 one day, PeterВҰ82011 stoodВҰ82009 up in the meeting of the believersВҰ82015 (aboutВҰ82028 120ВҰ82030 of them) andВҰ82019 saidВҰ82017,
\v 16 вҖңBrothersВҰ82033, it was necessaryВҰ82034 for the scriptureВҰ82038 to be fulfilledВҰ82036, where the holy \nd spiritВҰ82043\nd* had spokenВҰ82041 previouslyВҰ82041 through DavidВҰ82048 about YudasВҰ82050, the one who guidedВҰ82053 those thatВҰ82040 arrestedВҰ82055 \nd YeshuaВҰ82057\nd*
\v 17 because Yudas was one of us andВҰ82064 took his part in our workВҰ82070.
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 1:18-19: \xt Mat 27:3-8.\x*(Yudas had bought a field with the moneyВҰ82079 he had received for his treachery, and when he had fallen down \add in that field\add*, his stomach had burstВҰ82086 open and his intestinesВҰ82092 had slid out \add on the ground\add*.
\v 19 SoВҰ82095 everyone in Yerushalem started callingВҰ82104 that place вҖҳThe field of bloodВҰ82116вҖҷ.)
\p
\v 20 \x + \xo 1:20: a \xt Psa 69:25; \xo b \xt Psa 109:8.\x*Now it was writtenВҰ82117 in the scrollВҰ82120 of songsВҰ82121:
\q1 вҖҳLet his place becomeВҰ82122 desertedВҰ82126 with no one livingВҰ82132 there,вҖҷ
\m and
\q1 вҖҳLet anotherВҰ82141 person takeВҰ82140 his position.вҖҷ
\p
\v 21 SoВҰ82143 now it's appropriateВҰ82142 for one of the menВҰ82147 that has been with us for the whole timeВҰ82151 that the \nd masterВҰ82161 YeshuaВҰ82162\nd* was interacting with us,
\v 22 \x + \xo 1:22: a \xt Mat 3:16; Mrk 1:9; Luk 3:21; \xo b \xt Mrk 16:19; Luk 24:51.\x*from Yeshua's immersionВҰ82167 by Yohan untilВҰ82170 the dayВҰ82172 thatВҰ82173 he was lifted up from us \add into the clouds\add*вҖ”a witnessВҰ82177 of the resurrectionВҰ82179вҖ”to fill this position.
\p
\v 23 SoВҰ82187 theyВҰ82188 selected twoВҰ82190 men: Yosef BarsabbasВҰ82195 (nicknamed Justus) andВҰ82199 MatthiasВҰ82200.
\v 24 ThenВҰ82202 they requestedВҰ82203, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ82207\nd*, you know everyone's inner thoughts, so revealВҰ82210 to us whichВҰ82211 of theseВҰ82214 twoВҰ82216 thatВҰ82211 you have chosenВҰ82212
\v 25 to take this position of serviceВҰ82228 and being a missionaryвҖ”the position thatВҰ82234 YudasВҰ82236 deserted to go to his own place.вҖқ
\v 26 SoВҰ82245 they drew straws andВҰ82245 MatthiasВҰ82255 was marked so he was chosenВҰ82259 to join the elevenВҰ82263 missionaries.
\c 2
\s1 God's spirit arrives and many get saved
\rem /s1 The Coming of the Holy Spirit; The Holy Spirit Comes at Pentecost
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 2:1: \xt Lev 23:15-21; Deu 16:9-11.\x*WhenВҰ82265 the Day of Pentecost actually arrived, the believers met togetherВҰ82285 in the sameВҰ82289 roomВҰ82289.
\v 2 Suddenly there was a noise in the sky that soundedВҰ82297 like a strongВҰ82301 windВҰ82300, thenВҰ82290 itВҰ82304 filledВҰ82304 the entireВҰ82306 houseВҰ82308 whereВҰ82309 theyВҰ82310 were sittingВҰ82312.
\v 3 They saw what looked like tonguesВҰ82317 of fireВҰ82319 that kept dividingВҰ82316\f + \fr 3:1 \ft See https://www.billmounce.com/monday-with-mounce/what-%E2%80%9Cdivided-tongue%E2%80%9D-acts-2-3-0\f* andВҰ82320 thenВҰ82313 settling down on each one of them.
\v 4 In this way they were all filledВҰ82330 with the holy spirit andВҰ82329 beganВҰ82336 speaking in otherВҰ82339 languagesВҰ82340 as the spirit enabled them.
\p
\v 5 At the time, there were godlyВҰ82360 Jews stayingВҰ82356 in Yerushalem that had come from other countriesВҰ82365 all around the world.
\v 6 WhenВҰ82370 they heard this noise, lots of peopleВҰ82376 cameВҰ82374 to investigate butВҰ82370 they were confusedВҰ82378 becauseВҰ82380 they heard the believers talkingВҰ82389 in theirВҰ82393 own languagesВҰ82388 \add from around the world\add*.
\v 7 They were astoundedВҰ82394 andВҰ82398 marvelledВҰ82399, asking, вҖңWow, aren'tВҰ82403 theseВҰ82408 people talkingВҰ82411 all GalileansВҰ82413?
\v 8 SoВҰ82414 how come we're hearingВҰ82417 them speak the languagesВҰ82422 of the countries where we were born?
\v 9 There's people here from ParthiaВҰ82429, Media, Elam, MesopotamiaВҰ82438, YudeaВҰ82439, CappadociaВҰ82442, PontusВҰ82443, AsiaВҰ82446 \add Minor\add*,
\v 10 Frygia, Pamfylia, EgyptВҰ82451 \add (Mitsrayim)\add*, LibyaВҰ82457 (near CyreneВҰ82460), and visitorsВҰ82463 from Rome,
\v 11 CreteВҰ82470, and ArabiaВҰ82472. Some are Jews and some are non-Jews who've convertedВҰ82468 \add to Judaism\add*. And weВҰ82473 can hearВҰ82473 them talkingВҰ82474 about \nd GodВҰ82482\nd* in ourВҰ82477 languagesВҰ82478.вҖқ
\v 12 Everyone was amazedВҰ82483 andВҰ82486 totally puzzled, asking each other, вҖңWhat'sВҰ82497 going on here?вҖқ
\v 13 But othersВҰ82504 scoffedВҰ82506 and said, вҖңHa, they've just had too much to drink.вҖқ
\s1 Peter's sermon
\rem /s1 Peter Preaches to a Crowd; Peter Addresses the Crowd; Peter's Message
\p
\v 14 So the twelve stoodВҰ82517 up and PeterВҰ82520 told the crowd in a loud voiceВҰ82529, вҖңPeople of Yudea and everyone stayingВҰ82541 in Yerushalem. Listen to me so that I can explain this to you.
\v 15 This group isn'tВҰ82556 drunkВҰ82562 like you're all thinkingВҰ82560, becauseВҰ82566 it's still mid-morning,
\v 16 butВҰ82573 you're seeing what the prophetВҰ82580 YoelВҰ82581 wrote about:
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 2:17-21: \xt Yoel 2:28-32 (LXX).\x*God said, вҖҳIn the last daysВҰ82589 I'll pour out myВҰ82598 \nd spiritВҰ82597\nd* on all humanityвҖ”your children will tell of future events, your youngВҰ82617 men will see visionsВҰ82619, andВҰ82582 your old men will have dreamsВҰ82627 \add from God\add*.
\v 18 I'll pour my \nd spiritВҰ82652\nd* out on my male and female slavesВҰ82635 and they'll tell of future events.
\v 19 I'll do unusual things with the stars and planets, and also down on the earthВҰ82668 belowВҰ82669: bloodВҰ82670, fireВҰ82672, and clouds of smokeВҰ82675.
\v 20 I'll make the sunВҰ82677 go dark and the moonВҰ82685 go bloodВҰ82687 red. This will happen beforeВҰ82688 the greatВҰ82695 victorious dayВҰ82692 of the coming of \nd YahwehВҰ82693\nd*.
\v 21 ThenВҰ82698 everyoneВҰ82700 who relies on the nameВҰ82706 andВҰ82698 authority of \nd YahwehВҰ82708\nd* will be savedВҰ82709.вҖҷ
\p
\v 22 вҖңFellow Israelis, listenВҰ82712 to this account: You yourselvesВҰ82746 know thatВҰ82735 God did miraclesВҰ82729 through \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ82718\nd*, and he fulfilled signsВҰ82733 \add from the scriptures\add*вҖ”in fact God did this right in front of you.
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23: \xt Mat 27:35; Mrk 15:24; Luk 23:33; Yhn 19:18.\x*Then as part of God's plan and foreknowledgeВҰ82753, this Yeshua was taken to the authorities by those who didn't follow their own laws, and youВҰ82763 all killedВҰ82763 him by having him \add nailed to\add*\x + \xo 2:23: \xt Jhn 20:25.\x* a post.
\v 24 \x + \xo 2:24: \xt Mat 28:5-6; Mrk 16:6; Luk 24:5.\x*But \nd GodВҰ82766\nd* released him from the agoniesВҰ82770 of death and brought him back to lifeвҖ”death couldn't restrainВҰ82778 him.
\v 25 \x + \xo 2:25-28: \xt Psa 16:8-11 (LXX).\x*As DavidВҰ82782 wrote,
\q1 вҖҳI foresawВҰ82789 \nd YahwehВҰ82791\nd* always being in front of me. I refuse to be afraid becauseВҰ82797 he's there on myВҰ82800 rightВҰ82799.
\q1
\v 26 BecauseВҰ82805 of that, I was happy and spoke out myВҰ82808 praises. MyВҰ82808 whole bodyВҰ82821 lives in anticipation
\v 27 becauseВҰ82826 you'll never abandonВҰ82828 myВҰ82831 soulВҰ82830 in HadesВҰ82835, nor will you allow the godlyВҰ82839 one to decayВҰ82842.
\v 28 You showed me the roads to lifeВҰ82847. You fill me with gladnessВҰ82850 because of yourВҰ82855 presenceВҰ82854.вҖҷ
\p
\v 29 вҖңFellow Israelis, we can tell youВҰ82863 all with confidenceВҰ82861 that our patriarchВҰ82866 DavidВҰ82867 both diedВҰ82870 and was buriedВҰ82872, and hisВҰ82877 tombВҰ82876 is still here with us today.
\v 30 \x + \xo 2:30: \xt Psa 132:11; 2Sam 7:12-13.\x*SoВҰ82887 because he was a prophetВҰ82886, and knowingВҰ82891 that \nd GodВҰ82897\nd* has promised him to seat one of his descendants on his throneВҰ82916,
\v 31 he was foretelling the resurrectionВҰ82923 of the \nd messiahВҰ82925\nd* who was neitherВҰ82927 вҖҳabandonedВҰ82929 in HadesВҰ82936 nor did hisВҰ82941 bodyВҰ82940 decayВҰ82944.вҖҷ
\v 32 Then \nd GodВҰ82951\nd* raisedВҰ82949 this \nd Yeshua\nd* back to life and we're all witnessesВҰ82957 of thatВҰ82952.
\v 33 Now he's sitting at God's rightВҰ82962 handВҰ82962, and having receivedВҰ82976 the promiseВҰ82970 of the holy \nd spiritВҰ82972\nd* from the fatherВҰ82979, he pouredВҰ82980 this out whichВҰ82984 you're all seeingВҰ82990 and hearingВҰ82992 \add today\add*.
\v 34 \x + \xo 2:34-35: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*You see, DavidВҰ82995 never went up to the heavensВҰ82999, but he himselfВҰ83004 said,
\q1 вҖҳ\nd YahwehВҰ83008\nd* said to my \nd master\nd*: Sit down on my rightВҰ83015
\q1
\v 35 untilВҰ83017 I defeat yourВҰ83023 enemiesВҰ83022.вҖҷ
\p
\v 36 вҖңSo let all Yisrael \add (IsraelВҰ83035)\add* know that this \nd Yeshua\nd* that youВҰ83053 executedВҰ83054 on a post, \nd GodВҰ83047\nd* made himВҰ83040 both \nd YahwehВҰ83038\nd* andВҰ83041 \nd messiahВҰ83043\nd*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The First Converts
\p
\v 37 WhenВҰ83061 the people heardВҰ83060 that, they were deeply troubled and asked PeterВҰ83076 and the otherВҰ83079 missionaries, вҖңWhat should weВҰ83083 do thenВҰ83061, brothersВҰ83086?вҖқ
\p
\v 38 PeterВҰ83089 responded, вҖңTurn away \add from your sins\add* and each one of you needsВҰ83098 to be immersedВҰ83098 by the authority of \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ83108\nd*. ThenВҰ83090 your sins will be forgivenВҰ83110 and you all will receiveВҰ83116 the giftВҰ83118 of the holy \nd spiritВҰ83121\nd*,
\v 39 becauseВҰ83124 that promiseВҰ83127 is to you all and yourВҰ83132 childrenВҰ83130 and to their descendantsвҖ”to anyone who will call out to ourВҰ83146 \nd GodВҰ83145 YahwehВҰ83143\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 Then Peter shared further teaching with them andВҰ83154 encouraged them to save themselves out from this corrupt generationВҰ83161.
\v 41 Because of that, those who welcomedВҰ83170 hisВҰ83174 teaching were immersedВҰ83175 and aboutВҰ83185 threeВҰ83186 thousandВҰ83186 people were addedВҰ83177 to their numbers that dayВҰ83181.
\rem /s1 The Fellowship of the Believers
\v 42 They continued listening to the teachingВҰ83193 of the missionaries, and building their relationships with each other, and breakingВҰ83203 breadВҰ83205 and praying together.
\s1 The lifestyle of the early believers
\rem /s1 The Believers Meet Together; Life among the Believers
\p
\v 43 They were serious in their learning about God, and the missionaries did many miracles and signsВҰ83220 of God's power in Yerushalem and all the people wanted to be right with God.
\v 44 \x + \xo 2:44: \xt Acts 4:32-35.\x*All those who did believeВҰ83240 were united in purposeВҰ83244 andВҰ83245 had shared use of many things.
\v 45 Some sold their propertiesВҰ83253 and possessionsВҰ83258 and dividedВҰ83262 them among the group so that everyone had everything they needed.
\v 46 Each dayВҰ83276 theyВҰ83295 \add worshipped\add* together at the templeВҰ83283 andВҰ83277 also went to various homes to breakВҰ83290 breadВҰ83294 together. They talked about Yeshua at their mealtimes without sophistication,
\v 47 praisingВҰ83302 \nd GodВҰ83304\nd* and being popular with the peopleВҰ83312, and everyВҰ83319 dayВҰ83320 \nd YahwehВҰ83315\nd* was addingВҰ83316 more that were being savedВҰ83318.
\c 3
\s1 A lame man starts bouncing around
\rem /s1 Peter Heals a Crippled Beggar; A Lame Beggar Is Healed
\p
\v 1 One afternoon around 3pm, PeterВҰ83332 andВҰ83333 Yohan were goingВҰ83340 to the prayerВҰ83352 meeting in the templeВҰ83343.
\v 2 Now there was a manВҰ83359 who had been lame from birth, andВҰ83356 everyВҰ83370 dayВҰ83371 he was placed beside a doorВҰ83374 into the templeвҖ”an entry named вҖҳBeautifulВҰ83379 DoorвҖҷ. From there he could beg from the people enteringВҰ83386 the temple.
\v 3 He saw PeterВҰ83399 andВҰ83400 Yohan about to enterВҰ83404 into the templeВҰ83407, so he asked them for a donation,
\v 4 butВҰ83415 PeterВҰ83417 and Yohan, looking closely at himВҰ83420 saidВҰ83426, вҖңLook at us!вҖқ
\v 5 SoВҰ83432 the man grabbed onto them, expectingВҰ83436 to get given somethingВҰ83437 by them.
\v 6 ButВҰ83450 PeterВҰ83447 saidВҰ83443, вҖңI don'tВҰ83452 have any silver or goldВҰ83451, butВҰ83445 I'll give you what I do have. With the authority of \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ83465\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ83467\nd*, \add I command you\add* to walkВҰ83471.вҖқ
\v 7 ThenВҰ83472 Peter grabbedВҰ83473 the man by the rightВҰ83476 handВҰ83477 and pulled him upwards. Immediately the man's feetВҰ83488 and anklesВҰ83493 were strengthenedВҰ83485
\v 8 and he jumped up and stoodВҰ83496 and started walking and wentВҰ83501 into the templeВҰ83506 with them, walking and skipping and praisingВҰ83511 \nd GodВҰ83513\nd*.
\v 9 All the peopleВҰ83519 \add there\add* sawВҰ83515 himВҰ83520 walkingВҰ83521 andВҰ83522 praisingВҰ83523 \nd GodВҰ83526\nd*,
\v 10 and recognisingВҰ83527 that he was the man who usually sat \add outside\add* begging at the вҖҳBeautifulВҰ83545 DoorвҖҷ of the templeВҰ83550, they were astonished and astounded at what had happenedВҰ83560 to him.
\s1 Peter's sermon in the temple
\rem /s1 Peter Speaks to the Onlookers; Peter's Message in the Temple; Peter Speaks in Solomon's Portico
\p
\v 11 As the man clung onto PeterВҰ83572 and Yohan, all the peopleВҰ83585 ranВҰ83578 to see them in Solomon'sВҰ83599 Porch and they were really astoundedВҰ83600.
\rem /s1 Peter Preaches in the Temple
\v 12 But when PeterВҰ83605 saw \add the crowd\add*, he answeredВҰ83607 their thoughtsВҰ83623, вҖңFellow Israelis, why are you all puzzled about this, and why are you staring at us as if this man is walkingВҰ83636 because of \em our\em* powerВҰ83627 or closeness to God.вҖқ
\v 13 \x + \xo 3:13: \xt Exo 3:15.\x*The god of AbrahamВҰ83640, IsaacВҰ83644, and YacobВҰ83648вҖ”the god of ourВҰ83654 fathersВҰ83653вҖ”gave honour to hisВҰ83659 servantВҰ83658, \nd Yeshua\nd*, who you handed over \add to be killed\add* and then you rejected him when PilateВҰ83675 had judgedВҰ83677 him and wanted to release him.
