\v 34 None of them were lacking anything, becauseВҰ84758 any of them who owned propertiesВҰ84761 or housesВҰ84764 would sell them and donate the proceeds.
\v 35 They would lay them down in front of the missionaries, and from there itВҰ84782 was distributedВҰ84782 around according to what needs each person had.
\p
\v 36 Yosef (a Levite born in CyprusВҰ84809 who was nicknamed by the missionaries as вҖҳBarnabasВҰ84797вҖҷ, meaning вҖҳEncouragerвҖҷ) \add was one who\add*
