\p
\v 17 ButВҰ85200 the chiefВҰ85199 priestВҰ85199 and his colleagues who were members of the sect of SadduceesВҰ85209 were filledВҰ85210 with jealousyВҰ85211 and took action
\v 18 by having the missionaries arrestedВҰ85214 and thrown into the publicВҰ85227 jailВҰ85226.
\v 19 ButВҰ85253 one of \nd Yahweh's\nd* messengersВҰ85235 openedВҰ85244 the prisonВҰ85250 doorsВҰ85248 during the nightВҰ85241 andВҰ85253 led them out again, saying,
\v 20 вҖңNow go and stand in the templeВҰ85262 and keep telling the peopleВҰ85264 all the teaching about \add new\add* lifeВҰ85269.вҖқ
\v 21 SoВҰ85272 at dawn, having taken notice of the messenger, they wentВҰ85273 into the templeВҰ85279 and started teachingВҰ85281 \add the people there again\add*.
\p WhenВҰ85272 the chiefВҰ85286 priestВҰ85286 arrivedВҰ85282 with his companions, they called togetherВҰ85295 the \add religious\add* council and also the \add political\add* council of Yisrael, thenВҰ85272 called for the missionaries to be broughtВҰ85311 in from the prisonВҰ85310.
\v 22 ButВҰ85330 when their attendantsВҰ85319 got to the jail, they weren't there, so they returnedВҰ85329 to the gathering and told them,
\v 23 вҖңWe found the prisonВҰ85337 all locked up with the guardsВҰ85346 in their positions at the doorsВҰ85352, butВҰ85354 when they openedВҰ85353 it up, there was no one insideВҰ85355!вҖқ
\v 24 WhenВҰ85359 theyВҰ85360 heardВҰ85360 this, the officerВҰ85369 of the templeВҰ85371 andВҰ85372 the chiefВҰ85374 priestsВҰ85374 were totally puzzled as to what could have happened.
\v 25 Just then someoneВҰ85386 came in andВҰ85404 told them, вҖңHey, the menВҰ85393 that youВҰ85395 put in prisonВҰ85398 are in the templeВҰ85402вҖ”standing there teachingВҰ85405 the peopleВҰ85407.вҖқ
\v 26 So the temple officerВҰ85411 took the attendantsВҰ85414 and went and got them, but didn'tВҰ85419 use forceВҰ85421 becauseВҰ85424 they were afraid that the peopleВҰ85426 might start throwing rocks at them.
\p
\v 27 SoВҰ85432 theyВҰ85434 broughtВҰ85431 them in andВҰ85432 stood them in front of the councilВҰ85437, where the chiefВҰ85443 priestВҰ85443 addressed them,
\v 28 \x + \xo 5:28: \xt Mat 27:25.\x*вҖңWe officially commandedВҰ85447 you all not to be teaching in this nameВҰ85454 and authority. ButВҰ85456 seeВҰ85457 here, now you've filledВҰ85458 Yerushalem with yourВҰ85464 teaching, and what's more, you're blaming us for the death of that manВҰ85475.вҖқ
\v 29 ButВҰ85482 PeterВҰ85481 andВҰ85482 the other missionaries answeredВҰ85478, вҖңIt's better to obey \nd GodВҰ85489\nd* than peopleВҰ85492.
\v 30 The \nd godВҰ85501\nd* of ourВҰ85504 ancestorsВҰ85503 brought \nd Yeshua\nd* back to life after youВҰ85508 all handedВҰ85509 him over to be hung up on a pole.
\v 31 ButВҰ85517 \nd GodВҰ85515\nd* honoured this way-maker and saviourВҰ85518 by placing himВҰ85523 in the place of honour, to \add encourage\add* Yisrael to repentВҰ85526 and \add then\add* to forgiveВҰ85530 their sinsВҰ85531.
\v 32 We are witnessesВҰ85540 of theseВҰ85545 messagesВҰ85544, along with the holy \nd spiritВҰ85548\nd* who \nd GodВҰ85556\nd* gaveВҰ85554 to the ones who obey himВҰ85559.вҖқ
\p
\v 33 WhenВҰ85561 the gathered councils heardВҰ85562 this, they were enraged andВҰ85561 wanted to killВҰ85568 them,
\v 34 butВҰ85571 a certainВҰ85572 memberВҰ85579 of the Pharisee partyВҰ85579 named GamalielВҰ85581 stood up in the councilВҰ85577 chamber. He was a law teacherВҰ85582 respected by all the community, and he orderedВҰ85587 the \add guards\add* to take them outsideВҰ85590 for a while,
\v 35 thenВҰ85600 he saidВҰ85598, вҖңFellow Israelis, think carefully about what you're planning to do with theseВҰ85617 menВҰ85616.
\v 36 A while back, a man called TheudasВҰ85627 becameВҰ85661 prominent, sayingВҰ85628 that he was someoneВҰ85630 important. Eventually aboutВҰ85644 fourВҰ85646 hundredВҰ85646 others joinedВҰ85637 him, butВҰ85654 he was killedВҰ85649 and those who'd followed him were dispersedВҰ85659 and it all came to nothingВҰ85663.
\v 37 A bit later on, a GalileanВҰ85669 man named YudasВҰ85667 became prominent at the time of the census and he attracted peopleВҰ85677 to him. ButВҰ85675 he also died, and all those who'd been persuadedВҰ85690 by him ended up beingВҰ85690 scatteredВҰ85692.
\v 38 SoВҰ85693 here's my advice to youВҰ85699 all: pull back from \add killing\add* theseВҰ85704 menВҰ85703 and allowВҰ85706 them \add to continue\add*, becauseВҰ85713 if this teaching and goings on is man-made, it'll be overthrown,
\v 39 butВҰ85756 if it's from God, you all won'tВҰ85733 be able to bring them down in case you find yourselves opposing God.вҖқ
\p SoВҰ85756 they were persuadedВҰ85755 by Gamaliel,
\v 40 and after callingВҰ85759 in the missionaries and having them beaten, they commandedВҰ85763 them not to speakВҰ85767 using the nameВҰ85771 and authority of \nd YeshuaВҰ85773\nd* and then sentВҰ85775 them out.
\v 41 SoВҰ85779 the missionaries left the councilsВҰ85786, very excited that they were consideredВҰ85788 worthyВҰ85788 to be disgraced because of Yeshua.
\v 42 After that, theyВҰ85808 never stopped teachingВҰ85809 and preachingВҰ85811 the goodВҰ85811 messageВҰ85811 about \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ85815\nd* in the templeВҰ85803 and in various homes.
\c 6
\s1 Seven administrators appointed
\rem /s1 The church moves outwards; The Seven Helpers; The Choosing of the Seven; Seven Chosen to Serve; Seven Men Chosen to Serve
\p
\v 1 However around that time when the number of Yeshua-followers were growing, some of the Greek converts starting grumblingВҰ85828 about the Jewish believers becauseВҰ85834 the Greek widowsВҰ85843 were beingВҰ85835 overlookedВҰ85835 in the dailyВҰ85841 sharing \add of food andВҰ85819 money\add*.
\v 2 SoВҰ85851 the twelveВҰ85853 \add missionaries\add* assembled the believers together andВҰ85851 told them, вҖңWe're not pleasedВҰ85862 about having to take time off \add sharing\add* the messageВҰ85869 of \nd GodВҰ85871\nd* to be servingВҰ85872 here at the \add distribution\add* tablesВҰ85873.
\v 3 So brothersВҰ85881, look around youВҰ85885 for sevenВҰ85889 menВҰ85883 who are well known to be full of \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ85891\nd* andВҰ85893 wisdomВҰ85894, so weВҰ85896 can appointВҰ85896 them to be in charge of this part of the work.
\v 4 Then weВҰ85903 \add ourselves\add* can continue to pray andВҰ85908 share the messageВҰ85912.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 This idea pleasedВҰ85916 the group, so theyВҰ85928 went ahead and choseВҰ85928 StephenВҰ85931 (a manВҰ85932 full of faithВҰ85935 and of the holy \nd spiritВҰ85938\nd*), PhilipВҰ85942, Procorus, NicanorВҰ85946, TimonВҰ85948, ParmenasВҰ85950, and NicolasВҰ85952 (a non-Jew from AntiochВҰ85954 who had previously convertedВҰ85953 to Judaism).
\v 6 They stoodВҰ85958 these seven up in front of the missionaries, who prayedВҰ85966 andВҰ85964 then placed theirВҰ85969 handsВҰ85970 on them.
\p
\v 7 God's messageВҰ85973 continued spreading and the number of followers in Yerushalem was rapidly increasing, and a large number of the priestsВҰ85991 became believers.
\s1 Stephen gets arrested after teaching and doing miracles
\rem /s1 Stephen Is Arrested; The Arrest of Stephen; Stephen Seized
\p
\v 8 Now StephenВҰ85999 \add (one of the seven)\add* was full of graceВҰ86002 and power and was doingВҰ86006 miracles and amazing demonstrations of God's power amongВҰ86011 the peopleВҰ86013.
\v 9 ButВҰ86032 a group from the FreedmenВҰ86031 Synagogue as well as \add Jews\add* from CyreneВҰ86033, AlexandriaВҰ86035, CiliciaВҰ86039, and AsiaВҰ86041 \add Minor\add* rose up and started arguing against StephenВҰ86044,
\v 10 butВҰ86045 they weren't able to refute the wisdomВҰ86051 that he spoke \add with the help of\add* the pure \nd spiritВҰ86058\nd*.
\v 11 So theyВҰ86079 got some menВҰ86080 \add to falsely accuse Stephen\add* sayingВҰ86081, вҖңWe heardВҰ86084 himВҰ86085 denigrating Mosheh andВҰ86093 \nd GodВҰ86095\nd*.вҖқ
\v 12 SoВҰ86097 they stirredВҰ86096 up the peopleВҰ86099 and the eldersВҰ86102 and the law teachersВҰ86105 and so they approachedВҰ86107 \add Stephen\add* and arrested him and broughtВҰ86111 him to the councilВҰ86115 \add chambers\add*.
\v 13 There theyВҰ86117 produced the falseВҰ86120 witnessesВҰ86119 sayingВҰ86123, вҖңThis manВҰ86127 won'tВҰ86129 stop spreading messagesВҰ86134 against this holy \add temple\add* and against the law
\v 14 becauseВҰ86146 weВҰ86145 heardВҰ86145 himВҰ86147 sayingВҰ86148 that that \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ86152\nd* will be tearingВҰ86154 down this building andВҰ86158 will be changingВҰ86159 the traditions that Mosheh gaveВҰ86164 to us.вҖқ
\v 15 SoВҰ86167 thenВҰ86167 the councilВҰ86181 members lookedВҰ86168 across at Stephen andВҰ86167 saw that hisВҰ86186 face \add was shining\add* like that of one \add of God's\add* messengersВҰ86189.
\c 7
\s1 Stephen's history discourse and accusations
\rem /s1 Stephen's Speech to the Council; Stephen's Speech to the Sanhedrin; Stephen Addresses the Council
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ86195 the chiefВҰ86197 priestВҰ86197 asked \add Stephen\add*, вҖңIs all this true?вҖқ
\p
\v 2 \x + \xo 7:2-3: \xt Gen 12:1.\x*And he replied, вҖңMy brothersВҰ86211 andВҰ86207 fathersВҰ86213, please listenВҰ86214. OurВҰ86222 honoured \nd GodВҰ86216\nd* was seenВҰ86219 by ourВҰ86222 ancestor AbrahamВҰ86223 in MesopotamiaВҰ86227 beforeВҰ86228 he moved to HaranВҰ86233
\v 3 and he told him, вҖҳLeave your land and your relativesВҰ86247, and go to the place that I will show you.вҖҷ
\v 4 \x + \xo 7:4: a \xt Gen 11:31; \xo b \xt Gen 12:4.\x*SoВҰ86269 he left ChaldeaВҰ86264 and moved to HaranВҰ86268, and thenВҰ86269 afterВҰ86272 hisВҰ86277 fatherВҰ86276 died, he moved again to this land where we now live.
\v 5 \x + \xo 7:5: \xt Gen 12:7; 13:15; 15:18; 17:8.\x*Abraham hadn't received any land here as an inheritanceВҰ86301, in fact he'd never been near this land and nor did he have any childrenВҰ86328, yet God promisedВҰ86309 to giveВҰ86311 this \add entire\add* country to him and hisВҰ86321 descendantsВҰ86320.
\v 6 \x + \xo 7:6-7: \xt Gen 15:13-14.\x*And yet \nd GodВҰ86334\nd* \add also\add* told himВҰ86342 that hisВҰ86342 descendantsВҰ86340 would end up staying in anotherВҰ86346 country where they would be enslavedВҰ86348 and mistreatedВҰ86352 for fourВҰ86355 hundredВҰ86355 yearsВҰ86354.
\v 7 \x + \xo 7:7: \xt Exo 3:12.\x*However \nd GodВҰ86369\nd* promised to punish the nationВҰ86359 that enslaved them, and told him that in the end they would leave that placeВҰ86381 and serveВҰ86363 him here in this countryВҰ86359.
\v 8 \x + \xo 7:8: a \xt Gen 17:10-14; \xo b \xt Gen 21:2-4; \xo c \xt Gen 25:26; \xo d \xt Gen 29:31вҖ“35:18.\x*And he contracted with Abraham about being circumcised, and so when Abraham had Isaac, he circumcised him on the eighthВҰ86400 dayВҰ86397, and thenВҰ86383 Isaac went on to have Yacob, and Yacob to have the \add twelve\add* tribal leaders.
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 7:9: a \xt Gen 37:11; \xo b \xt Gen 37:28; \xo c \xt Gen 39:2,21.\x*Those brothers went on to become jealousВҰ86415 of Yosef andВҰ86412 sent him back into EgyptВҰ86420 \add as a slave\add*, butВҰ86412 \nd GodВҰ86424\nd* was with him
\v 10 \x + \xo 7:10: \xt Gen 41:39-41.\x*and rescuedВҰ86428 him out of all hisВҰ86434 troubles there. Then God gaveВҰ86436 him wisdomВҰ86441 and caused him to gain the favourВҰ86438 of \add Far'oh (PharaohВҰ86444)\add*, the kingВҰ86445 of Egypt, who then appointedВҰ86448 him as the ruler of all Egypt and over Far'oh's own householdВҰ86457.
\v 11 \x + \xo 7:11: \xt Gen 42:1-2.\x*ThenВҰ86461 a famineВҰ86462 hit all EgyptВҰ86470 and CanaanВҰ86472 causing greatВҰ86475 distress and ourВҰ86482 ancestorsВҰ86481 were unable to find enough food.
\v 12 But YacobВҰ86486 heardВҰ86483 that grainВҰ86488 was available in EgyptВҰ86492, so firstВҰ86501, he sentВҰ86494 off ourВҰ86500 tribal leaders.
\v 13 \x + \xo 7:13: a \xt Gen 45:1; \xo b \xt Gen 45:16.\x*On their secondВҰ86506 visit, Yosef revealed himself to them, andВҰ86513 so Far'oh becameВҰ86515 aware of Yosef's heritage.
\v 14 \x + \xo 7:14: a \xt Gen 45:9-10,17-18; \xo b \xt Gen 46:27 (LXX).\x*ThenВҰ86525 YosefВҰ86526 sentВҰ86524 for hisВҰ86531 fatherВҰ86530 YacobВҰ86528 andВҰ86533 all the extended familyвҖ”some seventy-five of them.
\v 15 \x + \xo 7:15: a \xt Gen 46:1-7; \xo b \xt Gen 49:33.\x*SoВҰ86544 YacobВҰ86547 wentВҰ86545 to EgyptВҰ86549, where he andВҰ86544 the \add twelve\add* tribal leaders eventually diedВҰ86551,
\v 16 \x + \xo 7:16: \xt Gen 23:3-16; 33:19; 50:7-13; Josh 24:32.\x*although their bodies were moved to Shekem where they were put into the tombВҰ86567 thatВҰ86569 AbrahamВҰ86571 had bought from the sonsВҰ86576 of Hamor.
\p
\v 17 \x + \xo 7:17-18: \xt Exo 1:7-8.\x*ButВҰ86602 as the timeВҰ86588 limit promisedВҰ86593 to AbrahamВҰ86598 by \nd GodВҰ86596\nd* was getting closer, \add our\add* peopleВҰ86601 multipliedВҰ86603 in EgyptВҰ86605
\v 18 untilВҰ86606 anotherВҰ86610 Far'oh \add (Pharaoh)\add* ended up ruling there who had never knownВҰ86616 Yosef.
\v 19 \x + \xo 7:19: a \xt Exo 1:10-11; \xo b \xt Exo 1:22.\x*He took advantageВҰ86623 of us Jews and mistreatedВҰ86627 ourВҰ86626 ancestorsВҰ86629, even forcing them apart from theirВҰ86637 own babiesВҰ86635 so they wouldn't live.
\v 20 \x + \xo 7:20: \xt Exo 2:2.\x*Mosheh was born during that timeВҰ86644 andВҰ86648 \nd GodВҰ86652\nd* considered him beautifulВҰ86650. He spent threeВҰ86656 monthsВҰ86655 in his \add own\add* father'sВҰ86661 houseВҰ86659
\v 21 \x + \xo 7:21: \xt Exo 2:3-10.\x*before being placed outside, from where Far'oh'sВҰ86676 daughterВҰ86675 tookВҰ86672 him andВҰ86666 broughtВҰ86678 him up herselfВҰ86681 as her own son.
\v 22 SoВҰ86684 Mosheh was instructedВҰ86685 in all the wisdomВҰ86691 of the Egyptians, and was a powerfulВҰ86697 speaker and project leader.
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 7:23-29: \xt Exo 2:11-15.\x*But when he hit fortyВҰ86710, it entered his mindВҰ86715 to visitВҰ86717 his relatives, the Israelis.
\v 24 WhenВҰ86724 he noticed one of them being mistreated, he retaliatedВҰ86731 and while defending the oppressed man, he struckВҰ86738 \add and killed\add* the Egyptian.
\v 25 He thought hisВҰ86759 relatives would understandВҰ86750 that \nd GodВҰ86756\nd* was bringing salvationВҰ86762 to them via himВҰ86759, butВҰ86766 theyВҰ86764 didn'tВҰ86767 see it that way.
\v 26 SoВҰ86771 on the followingВҰ86772 dayВҰ86773 when he saw two of them quarrellingВҰ86776, he tried to resolve the situation by saying, вҖҳMen, you're all brothersВҰ86793. Why are you injuringВҰ86798 each other?вҖҷ
\v 27 ButВҰ86813 the bullying one pushedВҰ86806 himВҰ86807 away andВҰ86813 saidВҰ86808, вҖҳWho made youВҰ86810 the judgeВҰ86814 over us?
\v 28 Do you want to killВҰ86819 me like you killedВҰ86825 that Egyptian yesterdayВҰ86826?вҖҷ
\v 29 \x + \xo 7:29: \xt Exo 18:3-4.\x*WhenВҰ86834 he heard that, Mosheh fled \add Egypt\add* andВҰ86834 becameВҰ86841 an exile in MidianВҰ86845 whereВҰ86846 he \add eventually\add* had twoВҰ86849 sonsВҰ86848.
\p
\v 30 \x + \xo 7:30-34: \xt Exo 3:1-10.\x*After another fortyВҰ86858 yearsВҰ86856, he was in the wildernessВҰ86863 around MtВҰ86865. SinaiВҰ86867 when he saw a messengerВҰ86868 in the flameВҰ86871 of a burning thornВҰ86875 bush.
\v 31 Mosheh was amazed at the visionВҰ86883 when he saw it, so he approachedВҰ86885 \add the bush\add* to look more closely when he heard Yahweh's voiceВҰ86891 saying,
\v 32 вҖҳI am the god of yourВҰ86905 ancestorsВҰ86904вҖ”the god of AbrahamВҰ86908 and of IsaacВҰ86912 and of YacobВҰ86916.вҖҷ At that point, Mosheh started tremblingВҰ86917 and was scared to go any closer to look,
\v 33 butВҰ86931 \nd YahwehВҰ86936\nd* saidВҰ86928, вҖҳTake off yourВҰ86945 sandalsВҰ86940, becauseВҰ86947 the groundВҰ86956 you're standing on is dedicated to God.
\v 34 I have noticedВҰ86962 the mistreatmentВҰ86964 of myВҰ86967 peopleВҰ86966 in Egypt and heardВҰ86976 theirВҰ86974 groaningВҰ86973 and so I cameВҰ86979 down to rescueВҰ86980 them, so now I'm going to sendВҰ86985 youВҰ86987 \add back\add* to Egypt.вҖҷ
\p
\v 35 \x + \xo 7:35: \xt Exo 2:14.\x*This was the same Mosheh that they had previously rejected and asked who had made him ruler and judgeВҰ87001 over them. Now \nd GodВҰ87006\nd* had indeed sent him as ruler and liberator by means of the messengerВҰ87018 that he saw in the thornВҰ87024 bush.
\v 36 \x + \xo 7:36: a \xt Exo 7:3; \xo b \xt Exo 14:21; \xo c \xt Num 14:33.\x*So eventually Mosheh led them out of EgyptВҰ87036 after doing miracles and signsВҰ87032 of God's power there, and then also at the Red Sea and during the forty yearsВҰ87046 in the wildernessВҰ87045.
\v 37 \x + \xo 7:37: \xt Deu 18:15,18.\x*This same Mosheh told Israelis that in the future \nd GodВҰ87062\nd* would raise up another prophetВҰ87057 like him from among them.
\v 38 \x + \xo 7:38: \xt Exo 19:1вҖ“20:17; Deu 5:1-33.\x*Now Mosheh was the person that \add led\add* the assemblyВҰ87081 \add of people\add* in the wildernessВҰ87084, was spoken to by one \add of God's\add* messengersВҰ87087 on MtВҰ87093. SinaiВҰ87094, andВҰ87095 one of ourВҰ87099 ancestorsВҰ87097 that receivedВҰ87102 livingВҰ87105 messages to pass on to us.
\p
\v 39 вҖңYet ourВҰ87117 ancestorsВҰ87116 didn'tВҰ87111 want to obey that man, so they rejected him and started thinking about EgyptВҰ87133 again,
\v 40 \x + \xo 7:40: \xt Exo 32:1.\x*saying to AaronВҰ87136, вҖҳMake some godsВҰ87139 for us to lead us becauseВҰ87144 we've got no idea what happened to that Mosheh who led us out of EgyptВҰ87154.вҖҷ
\v 41 \x + \xo 7:41: \xt Exo 32:2-6.\x*SoВҰ87161 together they made a calf as an idolВҰ87172 to bring sacrificesВҰ87170 to, andВҰ87161 they were pleased with what they'd achieved.
\v 42 \x + \xo 7:42-43: \xt Amos 5:25-27 (LXX).\x*ButВҰ87186 \nd GodВҰ87185\nd* turnedВҰ87181 and allowed them to serve the heavenlyВҰ87193 armies, just as the prophetsВҰ87199 wroteВҰ87195,
\q1 вҖҳIt wasn't me that you Israelis sacrificedВҰ87203 to for those forty yearsВҰ87206 in the wildernessВҰ87210.
\q1
\v 43 You turned to Molech's tent andВҰ87218 Refan's starВҰ87226 as yourВҰ87229 gods by making imagesВҰ87232 of them to bow down to. SoВҰ87218 for thatВҰ87234, I'll send you all away into exile beyondВҰ87244 Babylon.вҖҷ
\p
\v 44 \x + \xo 7:44: \xt Exo 25:9,40.\x*The tent of evidence was with ourВҰ87255 ancestorsВҰ87253 in the wildernessВҰ87258вҖ”made to the patternВҰ87272 that God had shown Mosheh.
\v 45 \x + \xo 7:45: \xt Josh 3:14-17.\x*OurВҰ87282 ancestorsВҰ87281 then carried thatВҰ87276 tent into the land, havingВҰ87279 inheritedВҰ87279 it along with Joshua from the possessionВҰ87288 of the pagans whichВҰ87276 \nd GodВҰ87294\nd* droveВҰ87292 out ahead of them. The tent remained there untilВҰ87301 the time of DavidВҰ87304
\v 46 \x + \xo 7:46: \xt 2Sam 7:1-16; 1Ch 17:1-14.\x*who foundВҰ87306 favourВҰ87307 with \nd GodВҰ87310\nd* andВҰ87311 requestedВҰ87312 to find a tent for the houseВҰ87317 of YacobВҰ87319,
\v 47 \x + \xo 7:47: \xt 1Ki 6:1-38; 2Ch 3:1-17.\x*butВҰ87321 it was SolomonВҰ87320 who builtВҰ87322 the houseВҰ87325 for God \add to reside in\add*.
\p
\v 48 However the highestВҰ87330 one doesn't actually live in structures made by people, butВҰ87326 as the prophetВҰ87340 wrote,
\q1
\v 49 \x + \xo 7:49-50: \xt Isa 66:1-2.\x*вҖҳHeaven is my throneВҰ87347,
\q1 andВҰ87350 the earthВҰ87351 is where I placeВҰ87365 my feetВҰ87354.
\q1 How could youВҰ87358 possibly buildВҰ87358 a suitable houseВҰ87357 for me?
\q1
\v 50 Wasn't it me that created everything?вҖҷ
\p
\v 51 \x + \xo 7:51: \xt Isa 63:10.\x*You stiff-necked people with uncircumcisedВҰ87380 heartsВҰ87385 and earsВҰ87389! You're alwaysВҰ87391 opposingВҰ87396 the holy \nd spiritВҰ87393\nd* just like yourВҰ87401 ancestorsВҰ87400 were.
\v 52 WhichВҰ87405 one of the prophetsВҰ87407 wasn't persecutedВҰ87409 by yourВҰ87413 ancestorsВҰ87412? Even the ones that foretoldВҰ87418 the coming of the righteousВҰ87424 one were killedВҰ87415 off by them in just the same way that you yourselves becameВҰ87432 his betrayersВҰ87428 andВҰ87414 murderersВҰ87430!
\v 53 You'd receivedВҰ87434 the law under the direction of messengersВҰ87439, andВҰ87440 yet you didn'tВҰ87441 obey itВҰ87442.вҖқ
\s1 Stephen's lynching and death
\rem /s1 The Stoning of Stephen
\p
\v 54 WhenВҰ87446 they heard that, they were raging inside andВҰ87446 gratingВҰ87454 theirВҰ87456 teethВҰ87457 at himВҰ87459.
\v 55 ButВҰ87474 beingВҰ87460 full of the holy \nd spiritВҰ87465\nd*, Stephen stared up into the sky andВҰ87474 was able to see God's splendour, as well as seeing \nd Yeshua\nd* standing there on God's rightВҰ87480.
\v 56 He saidВҰ87486, вҖңI can lookВҰ87487 through the sky that's openedВҰ87491 up and can see humanity's child standing at God's rightВҰ87500 side.вҖқ
\p
\v 57 At this point, they blocked theirВҰ87511 earsВҰ87510 and rushedВҰ87513 together to grab Stephen, yelling loudlyВҰ87507.
\v 58 They drove him out of the cityВҰ87522 andВҰ87517 thenВҰ87517 started throwingВҰ87518 rocks at him. His accusers left theirВҰ87532 cloaks in the care of a youngВҰ87537 manВҰ87537 namedВҰ87539 SaulВҰ87540.
\v 59 As StephenВҰ87544 was being hit by the rocks, he called out, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ87548 Yeshua\nd*, receiveВҰ87552 myВҰ87555 spiritВҰ87554.вҖқ
\v 60 ThenВҰ87557 falling to his kneesВҰ87559, just before he died he called out loudlyВҰ87563, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ87566\nd*, don'tВҰ87567 hold this sinВҰ87574 against them.вҖқ
\c 8
\p
\v 1 (And SaulВҰ87581 was agreeing thatВҰ87602 Stephen should be executed.)
\s1 Persecution of believers intensifies
\rem /s1 Persecution Scatters the Believers; The Church Persecuted and Scattered; The church in Judaea and Samaria; Saul Persecutes the Church
\p That same dayВҰ87593, intense persecutionВҰ87594 began againstВҰ87599 the assemblyВҰ87601 in Yerushalem, and so the believers fled throughoutВҰ87609 the regionsВҰ87611 of YudeaВҰ87613 and SamariaВҰ87615, exceptВҰ87616 for the twelve who stayed.
\v 2 (Some godlyВҰ87629 menВҰ87628 buriedВҰ87623 StephenВҰ87627 with loud wailing.)
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 8:3: \xt Acts 22:4-5; 26:9-11.\x*As for SaulВҰ87638, he started on destroying the assemblyВҰ87643 by enteringВҰ87647 people's homes and draggingВҰ87648 both men and womenВҰ87653 out and then off to prisonВҰ87657.
\s1 Philip preaches in Shomron/Samaria
\rem /s1 Philip Preaches in Samaria; Philip in Samaria; The Gospel Is Preached in Samaria
\p
\v 4 However, now the people who had fled began to proclaim the good message to others in other places.
\v 5 Around the same time, PhilipВҰ87667 went to a cityВҰ87672 in ShomronВҰ87675 \add (SamariaВҰ87675)\add* and told them about the \nd messiahВҰ87679\nd*.
\v 6 Crowds gathered and listened carefully to PhilipВҰ87694 and watched him do miraclesвҖ”
\v 7 many demon-possessed people shoutedВҰ87717 loudlyВҰ87720 as the demonsВҰ87716 left them, and many who were paralysedВҰ87725 or lame were healedВҰ87728
\v 8 so there were a lot of happy people there.
\s1 Simon the magician seeks power
\rem /s1 Simon the Sorcerer
\p
\v 9 One manВҰ87742 in the cityВҰ87751 had been practicingВҰ87752 magicВҰ87752 and amazingВҰ87754 the peopleВҰ87757, and he claimed that he was someoneВҰ87762 greatВҰ87764. His nameВҰ87745 was SimonВҰ87746
\v 10 and the people there from the least to the most important said, вҖңThis power is from the great \nd godВҰ87778\nd*.вҖқ
\v 11 They gave himВҰ87784 a lot of attention becauseВҰ87785 he'd been amazing them with magicВҰ87790 for quite a long timeВҰ87788.
\v 12 However when PhilipВҰ87798 started preachingВҰ87800 the good message about God's kingdomВҰ87805 and the name and authority of \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ87814\nd*, they believedВҰ87795 the message, and many men and womenВҰ87819 asked to be immersedВҰ87815 \add in water\add*.
\v 13 SimonВҰ87822 himselfВҰ87824 also believedВҰ87825 and was immersedВҰ87827, and thenВҰ87821 started accompanying PhilipВҰ87832 aroundвҖ”marvellingВҰ87844 as he observedВҰ87833 the miraclesВҰ87839 and signsВҰ87837 of God's power.
\p
\v 14 WhenВҰ87847 the missionaries in Yerushalem heardВҰ87846 that many people from ShomronВҰ87856 \add (SamariaВҰ87856)\add* had accepted God's messageВҰ87858, theyВҰ87862 sentВҰ87862 PeterВҰ87866 andВҰ87867 Yohan out to them
\v 15 so then they prayedВҰ87871 for them to receiveВҰ87875 the holy \nd spiritВҰ87876\nd*.
\v 16 (The holy spirit hadn't fallenВҰ87886 on any of them at that point, butВҰ87888 theyВҰ87890 had only been immersedВҰ87889 into the nameВҰ87893 and authority of the \nd masterВҰ87896 Yeshua\nd*.)
\v 17 So Peter and Yohan placed theirВҰ87902 handsВҰ87903 on the new believers and they receivedВҰ87907 the holy \nd spiritВҰ87908\nd*.
\p
\v 18 WhenВҰ87912 SimonВҰ87914 the magician saw that they received the \nd spiritВҰ87925\nd* after havingВҰ87910 the handsВҰ87920 of the missionaries placed on them, he offeredВҰ87928 moneyВҰ87931 to Peter andВҰ87912 Yohan, saying,
\v 19 вҖңGive me this authorityВҰ87938 so that anyone who I place \em my\em* handsВҰ87947 on will receiveВҰ87948 the holy \nd spiritВҰ87949\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 But PeterВҰ87951 respondedВҰ87953, вҖңMay your moneyВҰ87974 join you in your destructionВҰ87965 becauseВҰ87966 you thoughtВҰ87971 you could buy God's giftВҰ87968 with itВҰ87963.
\v 21 There'sВҰ87978 no role for you here and no part for you in our work becauseВҰ87988 yourВҰ87990 heartВҰ87989 isn'tВҰ87991 rightВҰ87993 with \nd GodВҰ87998\nd*.
\v 22 You need to turn away from this evilВҰ88003 \add desire\add* and beg the \nd masterВҰ88010\nd* that maybe he'll forgiveВҰ88014 you for yourВҰ88005 wrong intentionsВҰ88018
\v 23 becauseВҰ88024 I perceive that youВҰ88034 have a bitterВҰ88026 attitude andВҰ88028 ungodly habits.
\p
\v 24 SimonВҰ88039 answeredВҰ88036, вҖңOh, please ask the \nd masterВҰ88053\nd* on my behalf thatВҰ88065 none of what youВҰ88067 mentioned will happen to me.вҖқ
\s1 Philip immerses the Ethiopian official
\p
\v 25 After that, Peter and Yohan continued to testifyВҰ88077 and proclaim the good messageВҰ88082 about the \nd masterВҰ88085\nd* in many villagesВҰ88094 around ShomronВҰ88096 before they returnedВҰ88087 to Yerushalem.
\rem /s1 Philip and the Ethiopian Eunuch; Philip and the Ethiopian Official
\p
\v 26 Then a messengerВҰ88099 from \nd YahwehВҰ88101\nd* spokeВҰ88102 to PhilipВҰ88104, вҖңStart walking and head southВҰ88112 on the road thatВҰ88118 goes downhill from Yerushalem to GazaВҰ88124 through the wildernessВҰ88127.вҖқ
\v 27 SoВҰ88128 he headed off, andВҰ88128 \add on the road\add* he came across an important officialВҰ88136 of the EthiopianВҰ88134 queen\f + \fr 8:27 \ft Some translations list the queen's name as вҖҳCandaceвҖҷ, but that was the name of the series of queens, cf., Far'oh (Pharaoh) or Caesar which came to be used as a title for more than one person.\f* who was in charge of herВҰ88148 treasuryВҰ88147. This manВҰ88133 had been in Yerushalem to worship God
\v 28 and was returningВҰ88159 home in hisВҰ88165 chariotВҰ88164. As he rode, he was readingВҰ88167 \add the scroll of\add* the prophetВҰ88173 Yeshayah,
\v 29 and the \nd spiritВҰ88178\nd* told PhilipВҰ88180 to approach him and stay by the chariotВҰ88185.
\v 30 SoВҰ88189 PhilipВҰ88191 ran up to the chariot and heardВҰ88192 the man reading from the prophetВҰ88197 Yeshayah and asked, вҖңDo you know what it is that you'reВҰ88205 reading about?вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖңHow could I know when I don'tВҰ88217 have someoneВҰ88218 to guide me?вҖқ he answered, and so he invited PhilipВҰ88226 to climb up and sitВҰ88228 with him.
\v 32 Now the particular passageВҰ88233 thatВҰ88236 he was readingВҰ88237 was this:\x + \xo 8:32-33: \xt Isa 53:7-8 (LXX).\x*
\q1 вҖҳHe was led away like a sheepВҰ88241 being led to the slaughterhouseВҰ88243,
