\p
\v 37 в—ҳ
\v 38 SoВҰ88366 he commandedВҰ88367 \add the driver\add* to stop the chariotВҰ88370 and they both climbed down, and PhilipВҰ88379 immersedВҰ88384 the official in the waterВҰ88376.
\v 39 ButВҰ88404 as they came out of the waterВҰ88391, \nd Yahweh's spiritВҰ88392\nd* snatchedВҰ88401 PhilipВҰ88403 away and so the official never sawВҰ88406 him again, butВҰ88387 he continued on hisВҰ88416 journey very happy.
\v 40 As for PhilipВҰ88418, he foundВҰ88420 himself at \add the town of\add* AzotusВҰ88422, and as he passed throughВҰ88424 \add the coastal towns\add* on the way to CaesareaВҰ88435, he proclaimed the goodВҰ88425 messageВҰ88425 in each town.
\c 9
\s1 Yeshua talks to Saul
\rem /s1 The Conversion of Saul; Saul's Conversion
\r (Acts 22:6-16; 26:12-18)
\p
\v 1 Meanwhile SaulВҰ88438 was stillВҰ88440 spouting off murderousВҰ88444 threatsВҰ88442 towardsВҰ88445 the followers of the \nd masterВҰ88449\nd*. He went to the chiefВҰ88452 priestВҰ88452
\v 2 and obtained \add official\add* lettersВҰ88457 to enable him to enter the JewishВҰ88463 meetingВҰ88463 hallsВҰ88463 in DamascusВҰ88459 so that if he found either male or female followers of Yeshua, he could arrest them and bringВҰ88478 them to Yerushalem in chains.
\p
\v 3 On his journey as he approached DamascusВҰ88489, suddenlyВҰ88491 lightВҰ88496 from the skyВҰ88501 flashedВҰ88495 aroundВҰ88495 him.
\v 4 He dropped to his knees\f + \fr 9:4 \ft It seems most likely that Paul and company were walking to Damascus (and not on horseback despite paintings by Caravaggio and others). The journey of somewhere around 300km would have taken around two weeks.\f* and heardВҰ88507 a voiceВҰ88508 calling, вҖңSaul, Saul, why are youВҰ88515 persecutingВҰ88515 me?вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңWho are you, masterВҰ88521?вҖқ heВҰ88516 asked.
\p And the voice replied, вҖңI'm \nd Yeshua\nd*, the one that you'reВҰ88532 persecutingВҰ88533.
\v 6 Now, stand up and go into the cityВҰ88561, and you'll be told there what you need to do.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 Meanwhile his travellingВҰ88574 companions had stoodВҰ88576 there speechlessВҰ88577, because they'd heard the voiceВҰ88581 butВҰ88571 couldn't see anyoneВҰ88579.
\v 8 They helped SaulВҰ88589 up from the groundВҰ88592, butВҰ88587 even when he openedВҰ88593 hisВҰ88598 eyesВҰ88597, he couldn't see anything. SoВҰ88587 they had to lead him into DamascusВҰ88607 by handВҰ88602.
\v 9 Saul stayed there for threeВҰ88611 daysВҰ88610, unable to see andВҰ88614 not eating or drinking anything.
\s1 Ananias restores Saul's sight
\p
\v 10 Now there was a believer there in DamascusВҰ88626 named Ananias, andВҰ88622 the master spoke to him in a visionВҰ88636, calling, вҖңAnanias.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm here, master,вҖқ he answered.
\p
\v 11 SoВҰ88647 the \nd masterВҰ88648\nd* told himВҰ88650, вҖңGet up andВҰ88660 go to Yudas' houseВҰ88663 in StraightВҰ88659 Street where you'll find a man named SaulВҰ88665 from TarsusВҰ88667. He's prayingВҰ88670 right now
\v 12 and in his visionВҰ88675, he sawВҰ88672 a manВҰ88673 named AnaniasВҰ88678 who comes in and places his handsВҰ88686 on him so that he can receiveВҰ88688 his sightВҰ88688 back.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ButВҰ88690 AnaniasВҰ88692 resisted, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ88693\nd*, I've heardВҰ88695 a lot about that manВҰ88700, including all the evilВҰ88703 things he's done to yourВҰ88707 dedicated people in Yerushalem,
\v 14 andВҰ88712 the reason he's here in Damascus with the authorityВҰ88715 of the chiefВҰ88718 priestsВҰ88718 is to arrest everyone who trusts in youВҰ88725.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ88752 the \nd masterВҰ88731\nd* saidВҰ88726, вҖңGo now, becauseВҰ88733 I've chosen thatВҰ88740 manВҰ88739 to be a bearer of myВҰ88744 nameВҰ88743 and authority both in other countries, even to their kingsВҰ88750, and to the descendants of Yisrael,
\v 16 becauseВҰ88755 I'll be showingВҰ88756 him what he's going to have to sufferВҰ88765 for bearing myВҰ88764 nameВҰ88763.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ88768 AnaniasВҰ88769 left and wentВҰ88766 into Yudas' houseВҰ88774 where he placed his handsВҰ88780 on Saul and saidВҰ88783, вҖңBrother Saul, the \nd masterВҰ88787\nd* has sentВҰ88788 me hereвҖ”\nd Yeshua\nd* the one you saw on the roadВҰ88796 when you were comingВҰ88798 hereвҖ”so thatВҰ88797 you'll be able to see again and also be filledВҰ88803 with the holy \nd spiritВҰ88804\nd*.вҖқ
\v 18 Immediately somethingВҰ88808 like scalesВҰ88816 fell off Saul's eyesВҰ88812 and he was able to see again, and he got upВҰ88823 and got immersedВҰ88825 in water,
\v 19 before getting something to eat to renew his strengthВҰ88830.
\s1 Saul starts preaching in Damascus
\rem /s1 Saul Preaches in Damascus; Saul in Damascus and Jerusalem
\p ThenВҰ88832 Saul stayed several daysВҰ88840 with the believers in DamascusВҰ88838.
\v 20 He went straight into the JewishВҰ88847 meetingВҰ88847 hallsВҰ88847 andВҰ88843 started proclaimingВҰ88848 that \nd Yeshua\nd* is God's son.
\p
\v 21 The hearers were all amazedВҰ88859, sayingВҰ88867, вҖңIsn't this the guy that persecutedВҰ88872 the ones following that Yeshua in Yerushalem, and even came to Damascus to arrest them here and take them back to the chiefВҰ88895 priestsВҰ88895?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 ButВҰ88902 Saul was growing stronger\f + \fr 9:22 \ft It's not clear here whether it means that Saul was growing physically stronger, or that his preaching and debating skills were improving.\f* and he was confoundingВҰ88903 the Jews livingВҰ88907 in DamascusВҰ88909 as he taughtВҰ88910 them that Yeshua is the \add promised\add* \nd messiahВҰ88915\nd*.
\rem /s1 Saul Escapes from the Jews
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 9:23-25: \xt 2Cor 11:32-33.\x*After several daysВҰ88919, the religious Jews plottedВҰ88921 togetherВҰ88921 to killВҰ88924 himВҰ88925,
\v 24 butВҰ88935 SaulВҰ88929 found out about theirВҰ88932 plan. Those Jews were also watchingВҰ88934 the city exits so they could killВҰ88949 him if he tried leaving,
\v 25 butВҰ88951 hisВҰ88955 supporters took him to the city wall at nightВҰ88956 time and loweredВҰ88964 him down in a basketВҰ88966.
\s1 Saul goes to Yerushalem but has to leave
\rem /s1 Saul in Jerusalem
\p
\v 26 WhenВҰ88969 he got back to Yerushalem, Saul attemptedВҰ88976 to join in with the believers there butВҰ88981 they were all scared of him, not believingВҰ88986 that he was a true follower of Yeshua.
\v 27 However BarnabasВҰ88990 took Saul and broughtВҰ88994 him to the twelve, and Saul told them how he had seen the \nd masterВҰ89007\nd* on the roadВҰ89004, and been spoken to by him, and how he had spoken boldlyВҰ89016 in DamascusВҰ89015 in the nameВҰ89019 and authority of \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\v 28 SoВҰ89023 Saul stayed connected with the believers, goingВҰ89029 in and out of Yerushalem and speakingВҰ89035 boldlyВҰ89035 in the nameВҰ89038 and authority of the \nd masterВҰ89040\nd*.
\v 29 He also talked andВҰ89044 debatedВҰ89045 with the Greek-speaking Jews, butВҰ89052 theyВҰ89051 wanted to killВҰ89055 himВҰ89056,
\v 30 so when the brothersВҰ89061 found out, they took Saul down to CaesareaВҰ89066 \add on the coast\add*, and from there sentВҰ89068 him \add on a ship\add* to TarsusВҰ89072.
\p
\v 31 After that the assembliesВҰ89078\f + \fr 9:31 \ft Lit. вҖҳassemblyвҖҷ (singular). Jonathan Leeman in вҖҳOne AssemblyвҖҷ makes a good case that the force of ОәОұП„О¬ вҖҳthroughoutвҖҷ contributes to making the force of бјҗОәОәО»О·ПғОҜОұ plural in this sentence (similar to Luke's use in Luke 4:14, 23:5, Acts 9:42, 10:37).\f* of believers throughout YudeaВҰ89082 and GalileeВҰ89084 and ShomronВҰ89086 \add (SamariaВҰ89086)\add* had peaceВҰ89089 and grew in their respect and service of the \nd masterВҰ89099\nd*, as well as increasing in numbers through the encouragement of the holy \nd spiritВҰ89105\nd*.
\s1 Peter heals Aeneas
\rem /s1 Aeneas and Dorcas; Peter in Lydda and Joppa; The Healing of Aeneas; Peter Heals Aeneas and Raises Dorcas
\p
\v 32 PeterВҰ89110 travelled around the country andВҰ89109 thenВҰ89109 went to visit the dedicated believers in LyddaВҰ89122.
\v 33 He saw a paralysedВҰ89141 manВҰ89127 named Aeneas who'd spent eightВҰ89134 yearsВҰ89133 lyingВҰ89135 on his palletВҰ89138,
\v 34 and saidВҰ89143 to himВҰ89144, вҖңAeneas, \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ89154\nd* is healingВҰ89148 youВҰ89149. Stand up and pack up your bed.вҖқ And straight away Aeneas stood up
\v 35 and all the people livingВҰ89168 in LyddaВҰ89169 and SharonВҰ89173 who sawВҰ89163 himВҰ89165 became followers of the \nd masterВҰ89178\nd*.
\s1 Peter brings Tabitha back to life
\rem /s1 Peter in Lydda and Joppa
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ89181 in YoppaВҰ89180 there was a believer named TabithaВҰ89186 (or Dorcas if translated) andВҰ89197 sheВҰ89200 did a lot of goodВҰ89196 things as well as being generous to the poor.
\v 37 Around that time sheВҰ89208 got sick andВҰ89202 died. After washing herВҰ89212 body, theyВҰ89213 placed itВҰ89201 in an upperВҰ89217 roomВҰ89217,
\v 38 and since YoppaВҰ89224 was near LyddaВҰ89221 and the believers had heardВҰ89227 that PeterВҰ89229 was there, theyВҰ89233 quickly sentВҰ89233 twoВҰ89234 menВҰ89235 to request, вҖңPlease come as soon as possible.вҖқ
\v 39 SoВҰ89247 PeterВҰ89249 wentВҰ89250 with them, and when they arrivedВҰ89253 in Yoppa they took him up to the roomВҰ89259. All the widowsВҰ89265 stoodВҰ89261 there, sobbing and showingВҰ89268 him various clothesВҰ89271 that Tabitha had made for them.
\v 40 ButВҰ89308 Peter had them all removed from the room, and thenВҰ89308 kneeling down he prayedВҰ89298 before turning back to the bodyВҰ89303 and saidВҰ89304, вҖңTabithaВҰ89305, get up.вҖқ ThenВҰ89308 she openedВҰ89309 herВҰ89312 eyesВҰ89311, and seeing Peter there she satВҰ89317 up.
\v 41 Peter helped her to stand up, thenВҰ89320 he calledВҰ89326 the believers and the widowsВҰ89332, and presentedВҰ89336 the live Tabitha to them.
\v 42 News of this spread throughoutВҰ89342 YoppaВҰ89345 andВҰ89346 many people there believedВҰ89348 in the \nd masterВҰ89352\nd*.
\v 43 SoВҰ89354 PeterВҰ89362 stayed on there for quite a few daysВҰ89356, living with a tannerВҰ89366 of hides named SimonВҰ89365.
\c 10
\s1 Peter and Cornelius each hear from God
\rem /s1 Peter and Cornelius; Cornelius Calls for Peter
\p
\v 1 Just up in CaesareaВҰ89372 there was a Roman army commander named CorneliusВҰ89374 (leader of the вҖҳItalianВҰ89380 RegimentвҖҷ)
\v 2 who, along with all his householdВҰ89389, worshipped God and obeyed his laws. He gave to the poor and regularly asked God for help.
\v 3 One afternoon around 3pm he had a visionВҰ89405 where he clearlyВҰ89406 sawВҰ89403 one of God's messengersВҰ89414 comeВҰ89417 into the house and call, вҖңCorneliusВҰ89423.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Cornelius was scared and lookedВҰ89426 intentlyВҰ89426 and asked, вҖңWhat is it, masterВҰ89435?вҖқ
\p вҖңYourВҰ89441 prayersВҰ89440 and yourВҰ89441 helping the poor rose up to God's notice and attention,вҖқ he said.
\v 5 вҖңNow, send some messengers to YoppaВҰ89458 to go andВҰ89453 find a man there named SimonВҰ89462 PeterВҰ89469.
\v 6 He's staying with SimonВҰ89474 the tannerВҰ89476 whoseВҰ89477 houseВҰ89480 is by the seaВҰ89482.вҖқ
\v 7 SoВҰ89491 as soon as the messengerВҰ89494 left, Cornelius calledВҰ89500 twoВҰ89501 of his houseВҰ89503 servantsВҰ89503 andВҰ89505 a godlyВҰ89507 soldierВҰ89506 from his bodyguard,
\v 8 and after explainingВҰ89512 the task to them, he sentВҰ89518 them off to YoppaВҰ89522.
\rem /s1 Peter's Vision; Peter Visits Cornelius
\p
\v 9 The next dayВҰ89523 as they were approaching the townВҰ89531, PeterВҰ89534 wentВҰ89533 up onto the flat roof of the houseВҰ89537 around midday to pray.
\v 10 ButВҰ89547 he felt hungryВҰ89546 and wanted something to eat, butВҰ89545 while it was still being preparedВҰ89550 he fell into a tranceВҰ89560
\v 11 and saw the sky open up. Something like a sheetВҰ89573 was beingВҰ89581 lowered down to the earthВҰ89584 by the fourВҰ89575 cornersВҰ89576
\v 12 and it held all kinds of animals and reptilesВҰ89598, as well as birdsВҰ89603.
\v 13 ThenВҰ89606 he heard a voiceВҰ89608 saying, вҖңGet up PeterВҰ89612, and slaughter these and eatВҰ89615 them.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңI can't, \nd masterВҰ89621\nd*,вҖқ PeterВҰ89618 respondedВҰ89619, вҖңbecauseВҰ89622 I've neverВҰ89623 eaten anything that's forbidden.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ89630 the voiceВҰ89631 spoke a secondВҰ89636 timeВҰ89636, вҖңDon't youВҰ89643 be treating anything as unclean that \nd GodВҰ89641\nd* has made cleanВҰ89642.вҖқ
\v 16 This vision happened threeВҰ89651 times andВҰ89652 thenВҰ89648 the sheet thing was lifted back up into the sky.
\p
\v 17 NowВҰ89694 PeterВҰ89670 was still there wondering what the visionВҰ89676 was all about when the menВҰ89682 sentВҰ89684 by CorneliusВҰ89688 had tracked down the tanner's houseВҰ89692 andВҰ89663 arrived outside.
\v 18 They called out to ask if SimonВҰ89704 PeterВҰ89707 was staying there.
\p
\v 19 Even as PeterВҰ89712 still continuedВҰ89718 to ponderВҰ89714 aboutВҰ89715 the visionВҰ89717, the \nd spiritВҰ89722\nd* saidВҰ89718, вҖңHey, there's threeВҰ89727 menВҰ89725 here lookingВҰ89728 forВҰ89728 youВҰ89730.
\v 20 So get up andВҰ89735 go downstairs to them. Believe everything they say becauseВҰ89743 I sentВҰ89746 them here.вҖқ
\v 21 SoВҰ89750 he went down andВҰ89750 asked the menВҰ89756, вҖңI'm the one you're lookingВҰ89769 for, so tell me what you came here for.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 They answered, вҖңWe were sent by CorneliusВҰ89784 who's an army commander who worships \nd GodВҰ89792\nd* and obeys his laws and has a good reputation with you Jewish people. A holy messengerВҰ89804 told himВҰ89811 to sendВҰ89806 for you to come to his houseВҰ89810 so they can listenВҰ89813 to what you have to say.вҖқ
\v 23 SoВҰ89827 Peter invited them in to stay the night.
\rem /s1 Peter at Cornelius' House
\p The next dayВҰ89826, Peter andВҰ89835 some of the believersВҰ89838 from YoppaВҰ89842 started out with them
\v 24 and they arrived in CaesareaВҰ89854 the following dayВҰ89847. CorneliusВҰ89857 was expectingВҰ89860 them and had also invited some relativesВҰ89865 and closeВҰ89870 friendsВҰ89871 to join them.
\v 25 PeterВҰ89881 entered the house and when they met, CorneliusВҰ89898 knelt down and worshipped him
\v 26 butВҰ89911 PeterВҰ89912 pulled himВҰ89915 up and said, вҖңStand up. I'm just a man like you.вҖқ
\v 27 After they greeted each other, Peter wentВҰ89933 into the main room andВҰ89937 found that quite a few people had gathered there.
\v 28 ThenВҰ89943 he told them, вҖңYou all know that us Jews are forbidden by our laws to associate with or to enter the house of a non-Jew. However, \nd GodВҰ89966\nd* showedВҰ89968 me that it's not right to treat otherВҰ89959 people as beingВҰ89955 lesser or undesirable.
\v 29 That's why I cameВҰ89978 without any reservations when you sent for me. But I'm still waiting to know what you all want from me?вҖқ
\p
\v 30 SoВҰ89989 CorneliusВҰ89992 answered, вҖңI was prayingВҰ90013 in myВҰ90017 houseВҰ90016 three days ago in the middle of the afternoon when I suddenly saw a manВҰ90020 in shiningВҰ90026 clothesВҰ90025 standing in front of me
\v 31 and he said, вҖҳYourВҰ90032 prayerВҰ90035 has been heard, CorneliusВҰ90029, and \nd GodВҰ90046\nd* has noticed yourВҰ90032 gifts to the poor.
\v 32 Now he wants you to sendВҰ90047 messengers to get Simon, the one calledВҰ90055 PeterВҰ90056, from YoppaВҰ90050 where he's living by the seaВҰ90069 in Simon the tanner'sВҰ90065 houseВҰ90061.вҖҷ
\v 33 I did that straight away and you kindly came here, so now we're all here in God's \add sight\add* to find out everything that the \nd masterВҰ90115\nd* has commandedВҰ90109 you to say.вҖқ
\s1 Peter's talk in Caesarea
\rem /s1 Gentiles Hear the Good Message; The Gentiles Hear the Good News; Peter's Speech
\p
\v 34 SoВҰ90118 PeterВҰ90119 spoke up andВҰ90118 saidВҰ90124, вҖңHonestly, I'm still just realising that \nd GodВҰ90134\nd* doesn't favourВҰ90132 only certain people,\x + \xo 10:34: \xt Deu 10:17.\x*
\v 35 butВҰ90142 he acceptsВҰ90145 people from any nationВҰ90138 as long as they honour and obey him.
\v 36 He sent us a message through the descendants of YisraelвҖ”a good message that teaches that we can have peaceВҰ90159 through \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ90162\nd*вҖ”everyone's \nd masterВҰ90166\nd*.
\v 37 And you all know the news that started in GalileeВҰ90182 and spread throughВҰ90173 all YudeaВҰ90176 afterВҰ90183 the time of Yohan's teaching and ministry of immersionВҰ90185вҖ”
\v 38 how God filled \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ90192\nd* with the holy \nd spiritВҰ90199\nd* and with powerВҰ90203, and who then went around doingВҰ90209 goodВҰ90209 and healingВҰ90211 all those oppressedВҰ90214 by the devilВҰ90218, becauseВҰ90219 God was with him.
\v 39 We are witnessesВҰ90230 of all the things he did in the Jewish provinces and in Yerushalem, and thenВҰ90225 how they executed him \add by nailing him to\add*\x + \xo 10:39: \xt Jhn 20:25.\x* a stakeВҰ90249.
\v 40 Then \nd GodВҰ90252\nd* brought him back to life on the thirdВҰ90258 dayВҰ90260 and sent him where he could be seen,
\v 41 not by all the peopleВҰ90271, butВҰ90284 to the witnessesВҰ90273 thatВҰ90274 \nd GodВҰ90279\nd* had previouslyВҰ90275 appointedВҰ90275вҖ”to us who ateВҰ90282 with him and drankВҰ90285 with him afterВҰ90289 he'd been raised from the deadВҰ90294.
\v 42 He commandedВҰ90299 us to tell the peopleВҰ90303, and to testifyВҰ90305 that he is the one who \nd GodВҰ90314\nd* has designatedВҰ90311 to be the judgeВҰ90315 of the livingВҰ90316 and the deadВҰ90318.
\v 43 \add The writings of\add* all the prophetsВҰ90322 point towards him, and everyoneВҰ90331 who believesВҰ90333 \add thatВҰ90332 he's God\add* can have their sinsВҰ90325 forgivenВҰ90324 by hisВҰ90330 authority.вҖқ
\s1 God's spirit enters non-Jews
\rem /s1 The Gentiles Receive the Holy Spirit
\p
\v 44 While PeterВҰ90339 was stillВҰ90336 speakingВҰ90337, the holy \nd spiritВҰ90346\nd* came down onto everyone who was listening.
\v 45 The Jewish believersВҰ90360 who had come with PeterВҰ90365 were astonished that the giftВҰ90372 of the holy \nd spiritВҰ90375\nd* had been pouredВҰ90378 out even on non-Jews
\v 46 as theyВҰ90379 heard them speakingВҰ90382 in other languagesВҰ90383 andВҰ90384 magnifyingВҰ90385 \nd GodВҰ90387\nd*. Then PeterВҰ90393 said,
\v 47 вҖңSurelyВҰ90394 no one could argue against them getting immersedВҰ90404 in waterВҰ90396 now thatВҰ90402 they've receivedВҰ90412 the holy \nd spiritВҰ90409\nd* just like weВҰ90417 did?вҖқ
\v 48 So with the authority of \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ90431\nd*, he commandedВҰ90419 for them to be immersedВҰ90432 \add in water\add*. Then theyВҰ90435 askedВҰ90435 himВҰ90436 to stay with them for a few more daysВҰ90441.
\c 11
\s1 Peter explains everything to those in Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Peter Explains His Actions; Peter's Report to the Church at Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 Soon the missionaries andВҰ90451 other believersВҰ90454 in YudeaВҰ90462 heardВҰ90444 thatВҰ90456 non-Jews had also accepted God's messageВҰ90471,
\v 2 butВҰ90478 when PeterВҰ90481 wentВҰ90480 to Yerushalem, the strict Jewish believers were upset with himВҰ90523,
\v 3 sayingВҰ90527 that he had gone into the home of uncircumcisedВҰ90533 pagans andВҰ90536 \add even\add* eaten with them.
\p
\v 4 But PeterВҰ90544 started explainingВҰ90545 from the beginning,
\v 5 вҖңI was staying in YoppaВҰ90554, and as I was prayingВҰ90556 I sawВҰ90558 a visionВҰ90561 of an objectВҰ90564 like a sheetВҰ90567 comingВҰ90562 down, as if it was beingВҰ90571 let down out of the sky by its fourВҰ90569 cornersВҰ90570. As it cameВҰ90577 down to me
\v 6 I lookedВҰ90583 at it and sawВҰ90586 animals, even wild animals, and reptilesВҰ90596 and birdsВҰ90599.
\v 7 I also heardВҰ90603 a voiceВҰ90606 telling me, вҖҳPeterВҰ90613, get up and slaughter these and eatВҰ90616 them.вҖҷ
\v 8 But I saidВҰ90617, вҖҳ\nd MasterВҰ90620\nd*, I can't becauseВҰ90621 I've neverВҰ90627 eaten anything that's forbidden.вҖҷ
