\v 50 ButВҰ92946 the Jewish religious leadersВҰ92948 incitedВҰ92937 some prominentВҰ92944 womenВҰ92941 from the meeting halls and some from the local cityВҰ92950 government, and they then stirredВҰ92952 up persecutionВҰ92956 againstВҰ92957 PaulВҰ92959 and BarnabasВҰ92962 and had them expelled out of theirВҰ92969 regionВҰ92968.
\v 51 So Paul and Barnabas just left that place to face their own consequences, and continued on to IconiumВҰ92983.
\v 52 Meanwhile the believers \add back in Pisidian Antioch\add* were full of happiness andВҰ92991 of the holy \nd spiritВҰ92992\nd*.
\c 14
\s1 Paul and Barnabas in Iconium
\rem /s1 In Iconium
\p
\v 1 A similar thing happened in IconiumВҰ92997. Paul and Barnabas went into the JewishВҰ93006 meetingВҰ93006 hallВҰ93006 and spoke in such a way that a lot of both Jews and GreeksВҰ93020 believedВҰ93015.
